data.title: Louise of Great Britain
data.meta_description: Louise of Great Britain was Queen of Denmark and Norway from 1746 until her death, as the first wife of King Frederick V. She was the youngest surviving daughter of King George II of Great Britain and Caroline of Ansbach.
data.text:
"Princess Louise of Great Britain" redirects here. Not to be confused with Princess Louisa of Great Britain. For other princesses with the same name, see Louise of Great Britain (disambiguation).

Louise of Great Britain (originally Louisa; 18 December [O.S. 7 December] 1724 â€“ 19 December 1751)[lower-alpha 1] was Queen of Denmark and Norway from 1746 until her death, as the first wife of King Frederick V. She was the youngest surviving daughter of King George II of Great Britain and Caroline of Ansbach.
